stool vs chair back";s:4:"slug";s:19:"stool-vs-chair-back";s:5:"title";s:158:"Qazxsw Dressing Chair Dressing Stool Back Chair Bedroom Chair Comfortable Dining Chair Heart Shaped Comfortable Dining Chairs Dressing Chair Comfortable Chair";s:3:"alt";s:158:"qazxsw dressing chair dressing stool back chair bedroom chair comfortable dining chair heart shaped comfortable dining chairs dressing chair comfortable chair";s:3:"url";s:71:"https://i.pinimg.com/474x/4d/20/91/4d2091a96a24b4137a5d8673dc227af7.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSmoEkW2APGdc1sbKe3-7pspgBcifqwGcalHA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:355;s:6:"height";i:291;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/775111785857740872/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:58:{i:0;s:190:"A stool is a single seat on legs or a pedestal and without arms or a back while a chair is a seat especially for a single person usually with four legs and support for the back and the arms.";i:1;s:160:"These definitions however only give half the story since there are many similarities and differences between a stool and a chair that require in-depth analysis.";i:2;s:59:"Ergonomic design is a key factor when considering stool vs.";i:3;s:137:"Since backless stools lack lumbar support they are best for areas that see occasional or short-term use such as bars and breakfast nooks.";i:4;s:139:"Chairs with high backs and plush seats offer more structure inviting guests to settle in and dine comfortably for longer stretches of time.";i:5;s:45:"Chairs usually have a backrest and four legs.";i:6;s:42:"A stool differs from a chair in many ways.";i:7;s:46:"Firstly it does not have a back or an armrest.";i:8;s:62:"It is also usually shorter in height than a traditional chair.";i:9;s:53:"Chair and Stool are two different types of furniture.";i:10;s:46:"Their main function is to be used for sitting.";i:11;s:26:"However they do differ in.";i:12;s:159:"Ergonomic chairs are those that follow traditional chair design with some ergonomic tweaks to make sure that the chair fits perfectly the person sitting on it.";i:13;s:206:"Personalised adjustments like seat depth backrest tilt and armrest height etc not only provide optimal comfort but also the ultimate support that allows you to sit for hours without feeling much discomfort.";i:14;s:47:"What do people think of bar stools no backs vs.";i:15;s:56:"The ones with backs obviously provide some back support.";i:16;s:182:"But stools can be pushed all the way under the counter overhang which would give a tidier look and allow people who wanted to stand and maybe work at the counter easier access to it.";i:17;s:67:"Pull your shoulders back and keep your back flat against the chair.";i:18;s:44:"Do not lean forward as it leads to hunching.";i:19;s:34:"Rest your feet flat on the ground.";i:20;s:29:"Uncross your ankles and legs.";i:21;s:40:"This can put a strain on your alignment.";i:22;s:124:"Use a support tool such as a cushioned ergonomic chair to help keep your upper back straight and prevent you from slouching.";i:23;s:26:"Its a great middle-ground.";i:24;s:158:"Less sitting time - as more people become aware of the risks of excessive sitting a leaning stool or chair can significantly reduce the time spent in a chair.";i:25;s:43:"You are actively sitting to remain upright.";i:26;s:71:"While it burns fewer calories than standing it burns more than sitting.";i:27;s:390:"As nouns the difference between chair and stool is that chair is an item of furniture used to sit on or in comprising a seat legs back and sometimes arm rests for use by one person compare stool couch sofa settee loveseat and bench while stool is a seat for one person without a back or armrest or stool can be a plant from which layers are propagated by bending its branches into the soil.";i:28;s:138:"If you have found that you are not comfortable when using a standing desk with a chair then a stool may be the answer you are looking for.";i:29;s:65:"Stools are generally better for the back for a few major reasons.";i:30;s:70:"First a stool allows the back and spine to be in the natural position.";i:31;s:45:"This can help to alleviate excessive tension.";i:32;s:85:"After all there are times when you just want to sit back and relax when time permits.";i:33;s:97:"Which is why the Soutien Ergonomic Office Chair is another solution for your office seating woes.";i:34;s:137:"For starters the headrest and backrest will keep your posture in check as both are at the prime position for this ergonomic office chair.";i:35;s:77:"This chair also works for any height since it can be comfortably adjusted to.";i:36;s:24:"Chairs vs Stools Part I.";i:37;s:51:"September 30 2013 by nexus4112 in Culture Featured.";i:38;s:68:"A few years ago a very serious argument was brought up in the Nexus.";i:39;s:133:"A discrepancy of epic proportions wherein both sides fought it out in a battle not with swords and shields but with words and ideals.";i:40;s:95:"Weve come far enough as a society to just say no to stools in favor of chairs for back support.";i:41;s:53:"Backless chairs dont help health or personal comfort.";i:42;s:107:"Unlike other chairs the Learniture Active Learning Stool features a slightly concave rounded triangle form.";i:43;s:53:"This allows you to grab an item without falling over.";i:44;s:79:"The spinning motion is flawless and it only takes a few days to get used to it.";i:45;s:61:"Your back and core will thank you for using a backless stool.";i:46;s:90:"This style of stool offers some Lumbar support for the lower spine and for the lower back.";i:47;s:70:"A small backrest is not so visible above the height of the countertop.";i:48;s:80:"As the backrest is far smaller it will not offer complete support for your back.";i:49;s:97:"Like a backless stool a stool with a small backrest wont offer full support for younger children.";i:50;s:68:"A stool or saddle seat allows you to sit perch and move as you work.";i:51;s:208:"The higher seating position from a stool or saddle seat allows the thighs to slope downwards causing the pelvis and lumbar low back to be in a neutral position allowing the spine to achieve its natural curve.";i:52;s:64:"Wobble Stool VS High Drafting Chair For Standing Desk - YouTube.";i:53;s:54:"Wobble Stool VS High Drafting Chair For Standing Desk.";i:54;s:80:"A stool is generally distinguished from chairs by their lack of arms and a back.";i:55;s:116:"Variants exist with one two or five legs and these various stools are referred to by some people as backless chairs.";i:56;s:30:"Some modern stools have backs.";i:57;s:95:"Folding stools can become flat typically by rotating the seat to be parallel with fold-up legs.";}}